'''ESPN Xtra''' is a satellite radio station that combines the existing audio simulcast of ESPNEWS programs with sports talk programming produced by ESPN, most notably three local programs produced by [[ESPN Radio]] [[owned-and-operated station]]s.  This channel is on [[XM Satellite Radio|XM]]141.

The three shows added to the XM 141 lineup include The [[Michael Kay (sports broadcaster)|Michael Kay]] Show and The [[Max Kellerman]] Show both from [[WEPN]], and [[Randy Galloway|Galloway and Company]] from [[KESN]] (on a 4 hour delay). [[Bill Simmons]]'s ''The B.S. Report'' podcast from [http://www.espn.com ESPN.com] is also aired on the new channel<ref>{{cite press release |publisher=[[PR Newswire]] ''via'' xmradio.com |date=[[2008-01-28]] |url=http://xmradio.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=press_releases&item=1560 |title=ESPN and XM Satellite Radio to Launch 'ESPN Xtra' Radio Channel |accessdate=2008-01-28}}</ref>. In addition, the channel will air exclusive content to satellite radio throughout the year, and will include live events such as the [[ESPY Awards]] and the [[X Games]].

XM announced the addition of this channel on [[2008-01-28]].  [[Sirius Satellite Radio|Sirius]] announced changes to its audio simulcast of ESPNEWS, now called [[ESPN All Access]], on [[2007-12-11]], but will not be adding any content announced for XM as it will be exclusive to XM.

